'''Margaret Avery''' (born in [[Mangum, Oklahoma]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[singer]] and [[actor|actress]]. She was nominated for an [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] ([[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]], [[1985]]) for her role as Shug Avery in ''The Color Purple'' (the film of [[Alice Walker]]'s novel, filmed by [[Steven Spielberg]] with [[Whoopi Goldberg]]). 

